  "body": "Store forkchoice should never return zeros and rely on the consumes to convert zeros to genesis root. This is particularly dangerous because the consumers may not know or miss the conversion \r\n\r\nToday's pattern:\r\n```go\r\nfinalized, err := s.store.FinalizedCheckpt()\r\nfRoot := s.ensureRootNotZeros(bytesutil.ToBytes32(finalized.Root))\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat I propose:\r\n```go\r\nfunc (s *Store) FinalizedCheckpt() (*ethpb.Checkpoint, error) {\r\n        if s.finalizedCheckpt.Root == [32]byte{} && s.finalizedCheckpt.Epoch == 0 {\r\n            return &ethpb.Checkpoint{Root: genesisRoot}\r\n        }\r\n\treturn s.finalizedCheckpt, nil\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n ",
